      "content": "hey do u think companies like google or amazon actually have the tech right now to use stuff like smart lights or thermostats to track how someone is feeling? like if the lights dim right when im getting frustrated or the temp changes when im stressed... is that actually possible with affective computing or am i just imagining things?",
