    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get the \"user experience\" thing, but what if the user experience IS the experiment? like, if they have all this data on how someone reacts to subtle changes in their own home, and they use real-world people as the test group instead of just labs. it would be way more effective data for training their AI. wouldn't it be easier for them to just let the tech run and see what happens in real life?",
